title="Alex Nelson">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link
type="local"
href="ra-0003.xml"
addr="ra-0003"
title="Commutative Ring">Commutative Ring</fr:link>. An <fr:link
type="local"
href="ra-0011.xml"
addr="ra-0011"
title="Ideal">ideal</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[P\mathrel {\trianglelefteq } R]]></fr:tex> is <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Quasi-Prime</html:dfn> if for any <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a,b\in  R]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[ab\in  P]]></fr:tex>, then either <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  P]]></fr:tex> or <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b\in  P]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p><fr:p>If <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[P\mathrel {\triangleleft } R]]></fr:tex> is a proper quasi-prime ideal, then we say it is a <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Prime Ideal</html:dfn>.</fr:p>
 
   
